          <h3 class="reveal">What I Learned</h3>
          <ul class="reveal styled-list">
            <li><strong>Being the daily user changes everything.</strong> Every friction point I hit became a feature — auto-categorize, "mark all reviewed," the progress bar. Nothing stays broken when you use the tool yourself.</li>
            <li><strong>Accessibility assumptions need auditing.</strong> I assumed my minimal layouts were accessible. A real audit found six gaps. Fixing them taught me more than any checklist ever could.</li>
            <li><strong>Design data boundaries before writing UI.</strong> Preserving the localStorage data shape at the cloud adapter boundary meant zero component refactoring — the hardest architectural decision saved the most time.</li>
